IPSEC does not trigger alert when used to VPN. IPSec is the most secure protocol that works with VPNs.

Port 515 is used as an LPR/LPD port for most printers and older print servers. Port 631 is used for IPP for most modern printers and CUPS-based print servers. Port 9100 is used as a RAW port for most printers and is also known as the direct-IP port.

Metasploit can trigger buffer overflows in SCADA systems.

An MX record is used for outgoing (SMTP) and incoming (POP3/IMAP) traffic.

| **Kayıt Tipi** | **Anahtar Kelime / Kullanım** |
| **MX** | **E-posta**, SMTP, Mail Server |
| **A** | Host -> **IP (v4)** |
| **AAAA** | Host -> **IPv6** |
| **PTR** | IP -> Host (**Reverse Lookup** - Genellikle tarama tespitinde görülür) |
| **TXT** | **SPF, DKIM** (E-posta güvenliği, Spam önleme) |
| **SRV** | Servis konumu (Active Directory, VoIP vb.) |
| **NS** | Name Server (DNS sunucusunun kendisi) |

LDAP uses port 389 by default. 3389 is RDP. SLP is port 427.

