The net user command allows system administrators to manage user accounts on Windows PCs.

Wireless access points can utilize MAC filtering to ensure only known network interface cards are allowed to connect to the network.

Blowfish is a legacy symmetric encryption algorithm that is not PKI X.509 compliant due to its 64-bit block size vulnerability, unlike the industry-standard AES.

Non-repudiation occurs when a sender cannot claim they didn’t send an email when they did.

